00:45:21.670 --> 00:45:23.580
You still win with
probability a half.

00:45:23.580 --> 00:45:27.860
If you guessed right, you
win with probability 1,

00:45:27.860 --> 00:45:29.610
and there's some chance
you guessed right,

00:45:29.610 --> 00:45:33.250
so now you've got a
strategy that beats 50-50,

00:45:33.250 --> 00:45:35.970
because you guessed.

00:45:35.970 --> 00:45:39.040
OK, and this is a whole
field in computer science

00:45:39.040 --> 00:45:41.840
where you get randomized
algorithms, where

00:45:41.840 --> 00:45:46.760
this strategy depends on a
coin flip, on guessing a value.

00:45:46.760 --> 00:45:51.360
And it leads to getting
potentially a better outcome.

00:45:51.360 --> 00:45:53.260
All right, so let's
prove that now

00:45:53.260 --> 00:45:57.320
and see what the probability
is of winning with the guess

00:45:57.320 --> 00:45:59.468
strategy and what's
a good way to guess.

00:46:07.290 --> 00:46:10.780
So we're going to first
formalize our random protocol.

00:46:21.350 --> 00:46:30.500
All right, so if this
is the winning strategy,

00:46:30.500 --> 00:46:42.020
well first the envelopes
contain y and z,

00:46:42.020 --> 00:46:45.730
and they're in the
interval 0 to n.

00:46:45.730 --> 00:46:47.587
And y is going to
be less than z.

00:46:47.587 --> 00:46:49.170
That's how we're
going to define them.

00:46:49.170 --> 00:46:53.290
Now you don't know
y and z, but y

00:46:53.290 --> 00:46:56.730
is the smaller number in the
envelope, z is the larger.

00:46:56.730 --> 00:47:01.230
And in our example, n was 100.

00:47:01.230 --> 00:47:12.540
Now the player
chooses x randomly,

00:47:12.540 --> 00:47:18.800
uniformly among all the
possible half integers.

00:47:21.520 --> 00:47:26.230
So he might pick 1/2, he might
pick 1 and 1/2, 2 and 1/2,

00:47:26.230 --> 00:47:29.844
all the way out to n minus 1/2.

00:47:29.844 --> 00:47:32.010
You know, because if the
player picks anything else,

00:47:32.010 --> 00:47:33.500
it's useless.

00:47:33.500 --> 00:47:35.590
He won't have a chance to win.

00:47:35.590 --> 00:47:37.880
But he might, in
the case of 5 and 6,

00:47:37.880 --> 00:47:40.570
might have picked 5 and 1/2.

00:47:40.570 --> 00:47:44.100
And we're going to make our
random guess be equally likely

00:47:44.100 --> 00:47:48.060
among those n values, because
well he doesn't really

00:47:48.060 --> 00:47:52.290
know what the numbers are
I put in the envelopes.

00:47:52.290 --> 00:47:56.976
If he sees 6, he doesn't
know if it's 5 or it's 7, OK?

00:47:56.976 --> 00:47:59.350
So that's why we're going to
pick them all equally likely

00:47:59.350 --> 00:48:00.058
and it's uniform.

00:48:02.860 --> 00:48:07.850
Now the player is hoping
that he picked a value that

00:48:07.850 --> 00:48:12.500
splits y and z, OK?

00:48:12.500 --> 00:48:15.329
Because then he's going to win.

00:48:15.329 --> 00:48:17.620
If he picked an x between
the numbers in the envelopes,

00:48:17.620 --> 00:48:21.860
and follows the swap, if he got
the small number less than x,

00:48:21.860 --> 00:48:27.050
he's going to win, all right?

00:48:27.050 --> 00:48:41.100
Then the player opens a
random envelope, 50-50,

00:48:41.100 --> 00:48:47.340
to reveal a number r,
which is either y or z,

00:48:47.340 --> 00:48:51.730
but the player doesn't
know which one.

00:48:51.730 --> 00:48:55.690
So one of the numbers
gets revealed.

00:48:55.690 --> 00:49:03.100
And then the last step
is the player swaps

00:49:03.100 --> 00:49:08.720
if the number he revealed is
less than the guessed split

00:49:08.720 --> 00:49:09.220
number.

00:49:12.580 --> 00:49:16.400
That's the strategy,
and it's a strategy

00:49:16.400 --> 00:49:22.720
that depends on a random
guess or a random number.

00:49:26.302 --> 00:49:27.760
So let's figure
out the probability

00:49:27.760 --> 00:49:30.060
of winning with that strategy.

00:49:30.060 --> 00:49:33.640
And we're going to
use the tree method.

00:49:33.640 --> 00:49:37.410
Well, the first branch
in the tree method

00:49:37.410 --> 00:49:40.700
is whether or not--
where the guess wound up.

00:49:40.700 --> 00:49:42.770
And there's three cases
for how the guess did.

00:49:45.320 --> 00:49:48.660
You might have guessed
too low, in which case,

00:49:48.660 --> 00:49:53.590
x is less than y,
and y is less than z.

00:49:53.590 --> 00:49:57.130
You might have guessed
perfectly, in which case

00:49:57.130 --> 00:50:02.570
x is between y and z,
equals not possible.

00:50:02.570 --> 00:50:04.840
Or you might have
guessed too high,

00:50:04.840 --> 00:50:08.470
in which case y is less
than z is less than x.

00:50:08.470 --> 00:50:13.545
All right, so here's low,
here's high, and here's

00:50:13.545 --> 00:50:17.270
an OK guess, a good guess.

